Journal Club   UIC HOME ABOUT MISSION CONTACT Journal Club Department of Electrical   Computer Engineering University of Illinois at Chicago   WELCOME TO THE CLUB   What is our Club    r n                    Our Club is an opportunity for engaging with colleagues in a context of curiosity  uncertainty  and depth  Come explore interesting and unpredictable topics that stretch your horizons  It is a place for anyone in the UIC community to explore ideas and research that interests them  Journal Club effectively invites our community to say  this is what I am interested in  and or this is what I am thinking re each learning   You choose your article everyone is reading something different   There are amazing transdisciplinary themes that thread through each book or article  r n                     YOU DON T NEED TO PRESENT ANYTHING JUST COME  LISTEN  AND ENJOY THE DISCUSSION    n n n n n UIC  YOU DON T NEED TO PRESENT ANYTHING JUST COME  LISTEN  AND ENJOY THE DISCUSSION    n n n n OUR COMMITTEE   r n                        With a vision to accelerate interdisciplinary research this committe started the club  r n                     ZHICHUN ZHU  r n                        Computer Architecture  Parallel and Distributed Computing  and energy efficiency computer designs r n                          CHIRAG AGARWAL  r n                            Computer Vision  Machine Learning  Knowledge Transfer r n                         ARINDAM BOSE  r n                            Signal processing and Optimization theory r n                          OUR MISSION   r n                    This experience is meant to be informal  enjoyable  and intellectually stimulating  Journal Club is an opportunity to network with your colleagues from various schools  departments  and programs  Finally  Journal Club can be a platform for developing and improving teaching and presentation skills  r n                  Items to Know About Presenting   r n                    You don t have to present anything just come and join in the discussion   Each person who decides to present the article they re reading has up to    minutes to present  Please include the following in your presentation  r n                       What is the purpose of the reading and the apparent main focus of the article or book  r n                       What are your understanding of the article or book  r n                       What is your response to the author  r n                     Please email the presentation and or notes  as well as a pdf copy of your journal article or book chapter  if appropriate  to the  Chirag Agarwal so that he can distribute it to other attendees  r n                    Presentations are generally informal  and discussion is dynamic  n  Chirag Agarwal   When We Meet   r n                    Fridays          pm  r n                     SEL       r n                     Spring      r n                      https   www facebook com journalclubuic  n  https   www facebook com journalclubuic  CONTACT US    r n                            Feel free to contact us and be a part of the discussion     n 